            <!-- Contents -->
            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">A collection of 101 ḥadīth made by IA. It consists of
                     three parts; the first with 40 ḥadīth, the second with 40, and the third with
                     21. See Divine Sayings (Oxford, 2004) for edited text and translation.</note>
               <note type="structure"/>
               <note type="contentsNote"/>
            </noteGrp>
            <!-- Stemmatics -->
            <note type="stemmatics">OY lists 19 mss., of which at least nine can be considered
                  historic, although there are no autographs. The best is Beyazit 817 (in the hand
                  of al-Farghānī, pre-662H), Manisa 2989 (678H, copied from original) and Veliyuddin
                  1686 (c.667H, copied by a disciple of SQ’s.) The three parts are sometimes
                  separated in the collections.</note>
